                            <comment id="13019871" author="stack" created="Thu, 14 Apr 2011 15:43:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Will your change work on both windows and linux?  Can you suggest a change that will work for both?  Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13019884" author="mikaels" created="Thu, 14 Apr 2011 16:02:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Well no, because the NUL &quot;object&quot; is windows and not linux.&lt;br/&gt;
The right way to do is to have a check of the os runing and setting a variable DEV_NULL for example to be either NUL or /dev/null in the ruby script.&lt;br/&gt;
I don&apos;t know ruby yet so i cannot post the correct fix, just the idea.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Mikael.S&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13019951" author="stack" created="Thu, 14 Apr 2011 18:05:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This looks good and seems to do the right thing on my platform: &lt;a href=&quot;http://blog.emptyway.com/2009/11/03/proper-way-to-detect-windows-platform-in-ruby/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://blog.emptyway.com/2009/11/03/proper-way-to-detect-windows-platform-in-ruby/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Want to try it on windows?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If it works for you, I&apos;ll add it to head of hirb.rb and do a switch of /dev/null or NUL dependent on whether $WINDOZE is defined.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thnaks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13019990" author="mikaels" created="Thu, 14 Apr 2011 19:14:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok i will try, if it work i can prepare a patch if you want me to do so.&lt;br/&gt;
Anyway i&apos;ll keep you informed.&lt;br/&gt;
Mikael.S&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13020690" author="mikaels" created="Sat, 16 Apr 2011 23:14:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I presume this is required in 0.90.3 and up too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13020692" author="mikaels" created="Sat, 16 Apr 2011 23:14:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch for no method close under windows when starting hbase shell.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13021205" author="stack" created="Mon, 18 Apr 2011 19:47:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Applied to TRUNK.  Thanks for the patch Mikael.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13021207" author="stack" created="Mon, 18 Apr 2011 19:47:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh, you seem to not use the DEV_NULL you&apos;ve worked out in the patch... on commit I fix this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
